,{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) As it does not exist in the language of the Nabathæans, they change it into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"T","text_ar":"ط"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IF, TA.) [It is substituted for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotaEala","text_ar":"اِفْتَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the forms inflected therefrom when immediately following"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZ~alama","text_ar":"اِظَّلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZoZalama","text_ar":"اِظْظَلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZotalama","text_ar":"اِظْتَلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and it is substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*","text_ar":"ذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarakotuhu","text_ar":"تَرَكْتُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqiy*FA","text_ar":"وَقِيذًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqiyZFA","text_ar":"وَقِيظًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as is related on the authorities of ISk and Kr; and as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN jilo*aA='N","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ جِلْذَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiloZaA='N","text_ar":"جِلْظَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is mentioned in the Nawádir el-Aaráb. (TA.)       -A2-  [As a numeral, it denotes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nine hundred."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}